{
  "answer": "**The short anthem-like verse is the opening of Chapter 23 (\"Tarana-e-Milli\") in *Bang-E-Dara Part 3* by Allama Iqbal.**[^1]\n\n**The two apostrophes are:**\n\n**\"O Garden of Andalusia, do you recall the day, / When on your branches high our nest in safety lay?\"**[^2]\n\n**\"O wave of Tigris, you remember us, you know, / Your river tells our story in its flow.\"**[^3]\n\n[^1]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 3*, [Chapter 23: Tarana-e-Milli](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-3-cc61e8/23-tarana-e-milli/translation/).\n\n[^2]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 3*, [paragraph](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-3-cc61e8/23-tarana-e-milli/translation/#p-dea2e4).\n\n[^3]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 3*, [paragraph](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-3-cc61e8/23-tarana-e-milli/translation/#p-0bd01b).",
